theorem
((( i * p ) <> ( 0 ) & ( k mod ( i * p ) ) < p) implies ( k mod ( i * p ) ) = ( k mod p ))
proof
assume that
A1: ( i * p ) <> ( 0 )
and
A2: ( k mod ( i * p ) ) < p;
set T = ( k mod ( i * p ) );
consider n being Nat such that A3: k = ( ( ( i * p ) * n ) + T ) and T < ( i * p ) by A1,NAT_D:def 2;
k = ( ( p * ( i * n ) ) + T ) by A3;
then ( k mod p ) = ( T mod p ) by NAT_D:21
.= T by A2,NAT_D:24;
hence thesis;
end;
